translated: Hagberg, Eric, hospital doctor, Borås, b. June 9th, 1894 in Gothenburg to the wholesaler Gustaf H. and Matilda Kaijser. Married in 1922 to Gulli Zachau. Children: Bengt, b. 1923, graduated with a degree in medicine, Dagny, b. 1925, Ulf-Erik, b. 1932. Eric graduated from high school in Gothenburg in 1914, received his medical degree in Uppsala in 1918, and a medical licentiate in Stockholm in 1924. He served as an assistant and intern at the Seraf:las. x-ray institute from 1924-1925, an assistant physician at St. Eriks Hospital and temporary assistant physician at the Radiumhemmet in 1925, second assistant and later first assistant at Radiumhemmet in 1926 and 1927 respectively, an intern at the Seraf:las. x-ray institute in 1928, temporary chief physician at Radiumhemmet from 1928-1929, permanent second assistant physician at the Seraf:las. x-ray institute from 1929-1931, and hospital doctor at Borås las. x-ray department since 1931. Awarded the Royal Order of the North Star (RNO).
